sec.title:
Box 1 Classifying bat populations into susceptible (S), exposed (i.e. incubating infection; E), infectious (I) and recovered (immune; R) classes allows analysis of infection dynamics in bat populations. Three alternative model structures used to model the lyssavirus transmission period for different bat populations and their lyssaviruses are shown. Parameters are as follows: 
   b-birth rate; 
   β-transmission coefficient; γ-rate of recovery (seroconverstion); ε-disease-induced mortality; 
   d-’natural’ mortality; ρ-probability of infection causing disease
